						               													<description>Dead Man's Dice ... avast there ye swabs, 'tis a pirates' fast 'n' fun game o' dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games Above Board publishes the 2 to 6-player game ... with or without a bandana.  T-shirts also available.&amp;#10;Channel Craft publishes a 2-player version with red and black dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pirates take turns rolling (and then stacking) dice to build point-scoring piles o' treasure ... by matching like numbers, numbers in succession or sums of 7.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Plundering the opponent's dice is not only permitted but strongly advised.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pillaging is not recommended - you have been warned!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Beware the Jolly Roger &amp;hellip; double your points and seal victory or, if caught holding Dead Man's Dice, be keelhauled to subtract 7 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sending your opponent to Davy Jones' Locker by firing a broadside is one way to sink your opponent but it will cost you in doubloons.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Played round by round - the first to score a total of 100 doubloons (points) wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
